2 (15).
3 SECTION 3. The following agencies shall make available on the agency’s website contact
4 information for a person at the agency who is knowledgeable about each rule adopted,
5 amended or repealed by the agency:
6 (1) The Department of Environmental Quality.
7 (2) The Department of Transportation.
8 (3) The Department of State Lands.
9 (4) The State Department of Energy.
10 (5) The State Department of Geology and Mineral Industries.
11 SECTION 4. (1) Section 2 (2) of this 2026 Act applies to adoptions, amendments and re-
12 peals of rules with an effective date on or after January 1, 2027.
13 (2) Section 2 (3) of this 2026 Act applies to adoptions, amendments and repeals of rules
14 for which an agency provides notice of intended action on or after the effective date of this
15 2026 Act.
16 SECTION 5. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
17 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
